//Joint effusion


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 - Soft parts of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Joint effusion' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Minor' radio button is enabled
And 'Major' radio button is enabled
And 'Extensive' radio button is enabled
And 'Empyema' radio button is enabled
And 'Haemorrhagic' radio button is enabled
And 'Baker cyst' checkbox is enabled
And 'Synovial cyst prox. tibiofibular joint' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Haemorrhagic' radio button
Then 'Sedimentation' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Baker cyst' checkbox
Then 'Max. diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Max. longitudnal expansion' input field is enabled
And 'Torn' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Synovial cyst prox. tibiofibular joint' checkbox
Then 'Max. diameter' input field is enabled
